radiographic_examinations.findings: No pleural effusion, nodule, or opacity at the lung bases. Liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, and ureters within normal limits. A nonenhancing 1 cm simple cyst in the upper pole of the right kidney. Diverticulosis of the large bowel without evidence of diverticulitis. Mucosal enhancement and enlargement of the appendix measuring 7-8 mm. No free air or fluid in the peritoneal cavity. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. Diverticulosis of the sigmoid colon without evidence of diverticulitis.
